<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n53096m"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53096m">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53096m"> 96(m)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> emperor sitting on a / flat island</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Arthur himself is, in this tale, constantly referred to as &ldquo;the <mark>Emperor</mark>,&rdquo; and he is first met with &ldquo;<mark>sitting on a flat island</mark>&rdquo; below the Ford of the Cross on the Severn, &ldquo;with Bedwini the Bishop on one side of him, and Gwarthegydd, the son of Kaw, on the other.&rdquo; <small> W. Lewis Jones, <a name="WJKA3" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#WJKA3"><cite title="source">King Arthur in History and Legend</cite></a> (1914) 51</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
